properties.injury_desc:
Two lines caught in the front half of body.
Rope closer to front is a thing line cutting into the body.
The other one closer to the dorsal is a thick link and appears to have been on the whale for an extended period of time as there is growth on it.

Clear marking of rope scars, suggesting that rope has moved along body over time or there has been other rope entanglement in the past.

Some of the scars appear to be fresher than others.
properties.cause_of_stranding: Entanglement with discarded fishing gear/ghost nets
